Vice President Joe Biden released a statement on the retirement of Justice John Paul Stevens. Biden expressed his gratitude for Stevens' service to the country and his commitment to core Constitutional values. He praised Stevens' legacy as a justice, noting his humanity and fair application of the law. Biden also highlighted Stevens' service to the nation, including his enlistment during World War II and his expertise in antitrust law. He commended Stevens' work ethic and described him as an inspiration to generations of Americans.